???<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>What Is My IP Address (IPv4 & IPv6) | Thumbnail Generator Tools</title>
    <meta name="description" content="See your public IP address online. Check IPv4 and IPv6 instantly with a clean tool.">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="favicon-ip.svg">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style-win7.css">
    <style>
        /* Keep theme toggle aligned with light-mode palette */
        body:not(.dark-mode) .theme-switch {
            border-color: #9fc0e2;
            background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--nav-pill-1) 0%, var(--nav-pill-2) 100%);
            box-shadow:
                inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95),
                inset 0 -1px 0 rgba(116, 158, 205, 0.45),
                0 2px 8px rgba(40, 89, 149, 0.16);
        }
        body:not(.dark-mode) .theme-track {
            background: #6f95c1;
            box-shadow: inset 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        }
        body:not(.dark-mode) .theme-thumb {
            background: linear-gradient(180deg, #ffffff 0%, #e8edf4 100%);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <main class="app">
        <div class="headline-bar">
            <h1>What Is My IP Address - See Your Public Address - IPv4 & IPv6</h1>
            <div class="tools-group">
                <button type="button" class="theme-switch" data-theme-toggle aria-label="Toggle theme">
                    <span class="theme-icon sun" aria-hidden="true">&#9728;</span>
                    <span class="theme-track" aria-hidden="true"><span class="theme-thumb"></span></span>
                    <span class="theme-icon moon" aria-hidden="true">&#127769;</span>
                </button>
                <details class="tools-menu">
                    <summary class="tools-menu-trigger">All Tools</summary>
                    <div class="tools-menu-panel"></div>
                </details>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p class="subtitle">Instantly check your public IP in a clean and simple view.</p>

        <section class="card">
            <div class="convert-grid">
                <div>
                    <label for="ipv4Value">Public IPv4</label>
                    <input id="ipv4Value" type="text" readonly placeholder="Checking IPv4...">
                </div>
                <div>
                    <label for="ipv6Value">Public IPv6</label>
                    <input id="ipv6Value" type="text" readonly placeholder="Checking IPv6...">
                </div>
                <div class="full-row">
                    <label for="ipTypeValue">Detected Connection Type</label>
                    <input id="ipTypeValue" type="text" readonly placeholder="Checking...">
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="convert-actions">
                <button id="refreshIpBtn" type="button">Refresh IP</button>
                <button id="copyIpv4Btn" type="button" class="download-btn">Copy IPv4</button>
                <button id="copyIpv6Btn" type="button" class="download-btn">Copy IPv6</button>
            </div>
            <p id="ipStatus" class="status" aria-live="polite"></p>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-section">
            <h2>FAQ - Public IP Checker</h2>
            <div class="faq-list">
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary>What is shown here?</summary>
                    <p>This tool shows your current public IPv4 and IPv6 address if available on your network.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary>Why is IPv6 unavailable sometimes?</summary>
                    <p>Many internet providers and routers do not enable IPv6. In that case, IPv6 is shown as unavailable.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary>How often should I refresh?</summary>
                    <p>Refresh any time you change network, use VPN, or reconnect internet to see updated addresses.</p>
                </details>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <script src="tools-menu.js"></script>
    <script src="theme.js"></script>
    <script src="ip.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
